## Mermaid Diagram Requirements

- Each document must include **at least one** Mermaid diagram
- Node IDs should use only letters, numbers, and underscores
- Labels with special characters must be quoted: `A["Label with (parentheses)"]`
- All node names must correspond to actual classes/modules/components in the code
- All arrows must represent verified dependencies or data flows

### Diagram Type Selection

| Topic Type | Primary Diagram | Secondary Diagram |
|-----------|----------------|-------------------|
| Service/Component | flowchart TD — Architecture & dependencies | sequenceDiagram — Interaction flow |
| API/Endpoint | sequenceDiagram — Request lifecycle | flowchart TD — Error handling |
| Data Model | erDiagram — Entity relationships | flowchart TD — Data lifecycle |
| Workflow | flowchart TD — Process steps & decisions | sequenceDiagram — Participant interactions |

